(We now move to a turning point in Modern Indian History.)

1ï¸âƒ£ Core Teaching (Simple, Exam-Oriented)
ğŸ”¹ Why Revolt of 1857 is Important

First large-scale revolt against British rule

Called:

First War of Independence (by nationalists)

Sepoy Mutiny (by British historians)

Marked end of East India Company rule

ğŸ“Œ UPSC Focus: Causes + centres + leaders + consequences.

ğŸ”µ Causes of Revolt
1ï¸âƒ£ Political Causes

Doctrine of Lapse (Dalhousie)

Annexation of Awadh

Loss of royal privileges

2ï¸âƒ£ Economic Causes

Heavy land revenue

Exploitation of peasants

Decline of traditional industries

3ï¸âƒ£ Military Causes

Discrimination against Indian soldiers

Low salary & promotion barriers

4ï¸âƒ£ Immediate Cause

Introduction of Enfield rifle cartridges

Greased with cow & pig fat

Hurt religious sentiments

ğŸ“Œ Spark began at Meerut (10 May 1857).

ğŸ”´ Major Centres & Leaders
Centre	Leader
Delhi	Bahadur Shah Zafar
Kanpur	Nana Sahib
Jhansi	Rani Lakshmibai
Lucknow	Begum Hazrat Mahal
Bihar	Kunwar Singh
ğŸ”¹ Nature of Revolt

Mainly North & Central India

Limited participation in South India

No unified leadership

Lacked modern weapons

ğŸ”¹ Consequences

End of East India Company (1858)

Government of India Act 1858

Crown rule began

Army reorganised

Policy of non-interference in religion

ğŸ“Œ British became cautious rulers.

